    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gradient-heated devices used to determine the melting point of a substance designed by Ludwig Kofler, usually to be used with a microscope. These feature stainless steel surfaces which are electrically heated at one end, resulting in an approximately linear temperature gradient along the top surface.</Note_Text>
